cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.MM

The paper deals with the modeling and analysis of molecular communication systems, which involves the transmission of information using chemical molecules. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI), as well as systems and control (cs.SY), mathematical analysis (cs.MA), and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of stochastic geometry to model the positions of randomly-placed transmitters also suggests a connection to probability (cs.PR) and optimization (cs.LG). However, given the focus on communication and networking, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories.
